    "63 classified the DTI prediction methods into the \"topdown\" method, which indirectly computes from observable features as raw materials, and the \"bottom-up\" method, which directly computes from information about molecular structures or sequences.",
    "Moon et al.",
    "64 proposed two key enhancement strategies to address the underperformance of the generalization ability of deep learning models by introducing the information equation of physics to capture the energy component of the interaction force of atom-atom pairs at the four levels and enhancing the generalization ability through data enhancement to improve the generalization capability.",
    "(3) Return to single drug analysis: the assessment of the predictive effectiveness of the model ultimately comes down to the predictive accuracy of a single drug.",
    "Grounding the prediction of DTIs to the level of a single-drug application is also a focus of DTIs research."
